<meta name="assert" content="The 'flex-grow' property is invalid when the property applied to flex container."><title>
</title><style>
  #container {
    background-color: green;
    display: flex;
    flex-grow: 2;
    height: 100px;
    width: 100px;
  }
  #container div {
    background-color: red;
    height: 100px;
    width: 0px;
  }
  #cover {
    background-color: green;
    height: 4294967297px;
    position: relative;
    top: -100px;
    width: 50px;
  }
</style>
<body>
  <p>Test passes if there is a filled green square and <strong>no red</strong>.</p>
  <title>CSS Flexbox Test: flex-grow - (invalid when applied to flex container)</title>
